 There is another mass abduction that has been reported in Nigeria. And in this latest incident, nearly about 317 school girls have been abducted by armed bandits in the Zamfara. The attack by armed men on the Government Girls Secondary School, Jangebe in Talata Mafara Local Government Area of Zamfara State happened on Friday morning. Zailani Bappa, the spokesperson to the Zamfara State Governor, Bello Matawalle, told PREMIUM TIMES Friday morning that the exact number of students kidnapped has not been ascertained. He said the state government is working with security operatives to ascertain the details of the kidnap and ensure the kidnapped victims are freed. A teacher in the school had told the BBC Hausa that about 300 female students were kidnapped.